  "doc_id": "48330",
  "text": "Under and overstating of perinephric invasion are the most common staging errors at CT [CITATION_1] . The most specific finding of stage T3a, the presence of an enhanced nodule in the perinephric space, is highly specific but also low sensitive. The differentiation between stage T2 and T3a tumors is very problematic.",
